			</td>
			<td valign="top">
				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">My favorite method for cleaning the edge connector is to find a bowl with a flat bottom...maybe one that margarine comes in or something (cleaned out thoroughly, of course).  Then, fill the bowl with a bout 3/8 of an inch of rubbing alcohol.  Using a soft-bristled toothbrush, place the dirty edge connector in the bowl and scrub away all the grime.  Let it dry thoroughly and you should be golden.
<br />
<br />-Rob</div>

