						<div class="postbody">I remember doing something in Chemistry where I had to line a bowl with tin foil, and pour boiling baking soda water in it. If you drop a silver coin in it, a chemical reaction similar to what happens in a battery occurs, and all of the crud on the coin will be removed, adhering to the tin foil. But I don't know if you'd want to put your NES games in boiling baking soda water  <img src="./images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" /> . And I don't know how much this would work with NES contacts (it's probably to clean silver only).</div>

